Package frame

This package contains everything that works with rendering and processing of resources to the screen, as well as the screen itself.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GameFrame
    GameFrame is a class used to store the GamePanel to provide the user with access to the game.
    GameGraphics
    GameGraphics merges all the maps used into the game into one location, which allows interaction to be done between the player and the terrain.
    GameMouse
    The GameMouse class is used to provide interaction with the mouse, without creating unnecessary clutter in the GamePanel class.
    GameMusic
    GameMusic provides everything required to play background music.
    GamePanel
    GamePanel accomplishes two tasks.

Package frame Description

This package contains everything that works with rendering and processing of resources to the screen, as well as the screen itself.

Changes: The package now supports a fully functioning processor, both from a logic and rendering perspective.
